race.comment: BEEN OUR ANGEL (1) gave a great sight first-up in town when only nabbed late by the rejuvenated Bristler. Didn't show the same tenacity last time but was slow to recover. Peaking now and looks the one to beat. MISLUDI (9) was too bad to be true last start in town but her first two runs of the prep were full of merit. Finds her easiest assignment in some time and can rebound. TRULY ELSA (3) has only been fair in her resuming efforts but strips fitter third-up and should find this easier. Holder takes over and is worth some thought. FASHION DOG (2) surprised the market when resuming with a barnstorming win at Strathalbyn. Has kept the legs ticking over with a trial 26 days between runs and deserves more respect this time.
